headline_main: Notre-Dame, Columbine, Beyoncé: Your Wednesday Briefing

snippet: While other presidents sought to broaden their public support, President Trump is sticking with the voters who first propelled him to the White House.
lead_paragraph: Good Wednesday morning. Here are some of the stories making news in Washington and politics today.
abstract: While other presidents sought to broaden their public support, President Trump is sticking with the voters who first propelled him to the White House.
headline_main: On Politics: Trump’s United Base of America

snippet: Mr. Biden once called Fritz Hollings his best friend in the Senate, strengthening his connection to the state, which is pivotal in the Democratic primary.
lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Tuesday remembered Ernest F. Hollings as “a giant in this state and nation” who evolved to “write the great story of our times.”
abstract: Mr. Biden once called Fritz Hollings his best friend in the Senate, strengthening his connection to the state, which is pivotal in the Democratic primary.

snippet: Bernie Sanders is the money leader. Elizabeth Warren is spending big. Pete Buttigieg emerged out of nowhere. And (almost) everyone is buying gobs of Facebook ads.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic challengers to President Trump raised tens of millions of dollars in the first months of the 2020 presidential campaign, with Senator Bernie Sanders setting the pace for the field, with $18.2 million raised.

snippet: The establishment gets a bit of a break, but not as much as might be expected.
lead_paragraph: Caucuses have long been the bane of the political establishment and a boost to activist-backed presidential candidates, whether it’s Ted Cruz on the right or Bernie Sanders on the left.

snippet: In the On Politics newsletter: Why looking at Democratic voters through social media offers a skewed view of the party’s demographics and ideology.
lead_paragraph: Hi. Welcome to On Politics, your guide to the day in national politics. I’m Lisa Lerer, your host.
